#### **Summary  `cal` command in Linux, which is used to display calendars in the terminal
command -v cal
sudo apt update
sudo apt install ncal
# For other distributions, install the `util-linux` package using your package manager.
cal
cal -y  # Display Calendar for Entire Current Year**:
cal 1982
cal 8 1982   #   cal [month] [year]
cal -3 # **Show a Three-Month Calendar (Current, Previous, and Next Months)**
